   8:../Core/Src/adc_isr.c **** /**
   9:../Core/Src/adc_isr.c ****  * This interrupt is called every time a single ADC conversion is completed.
  10:../Core/Src/adc_isr.c ****  * Through adc[1-3]_conv_ptr, we keep track of which channel we are currently
  11:../Core/Src/adc_isr.c ****  * converting. We then store the value in the appropriate field of the
  12:../Core/Src/adc_isr.c ****  * analog_feedback_data struct in the global state. If we have finished
  13:../Core/Src/adc_isr.c ****  * converting all channels in the sequence, we start the next ADC.
  14:../Core/Src/adc_isr.c ****  * 
  15:../Core/Src/adc_isr.c ****  * The sequence of channels for each ADC is defined in port_config.h as well
  16:../Core/Src/adc_isr.c ****  * as the sequence of ADCs to convert.
  17:../Core/Src/adc_isr.c ****  */
